            NAME            NAME
            make.label - Draws text labels on the map composition at a
            point location of a GRASS or MAPGEN sites file.
            
            SYNOPSIS            SYNOPSIS
            make.label [filename]            make.label                                   ________ 
            
            DESCRIPTION            DESCRIPTION
            make.label constructs map labels from a MAPGEN sites file in            __________                                                  
            the sites_geo directory.  GRASS sites, attribute, or                _________                                       
            category files can be used and are converted to MAPGEN sites
            files during this process.
            
            The user is required to provide the following:
            
                 - MAPGEN sites file name
                 - overlay file name (if not specified in the command
                      line)
                 - map definition file name
                 - plotter pen number
                 - text font
                 - text size
                 - text rotation angle
                 - label justification
                 - x coordinate offset
                 - y coordinate offset
            
            Completing the response sequence generates the required
            files to construct the map element.  Definition parameters
            are stored in the labels directory; graphic elements to draw                              ______                                    
            the map on the screen or plotter are stored in the ovm                                                               ___
            directory.  The default file name for both directories is
            the sites file name, suffixed with ".l", where l denotes a                                                __                    
            label file.
            
            Changing the appearance of the label (e.g. label size or
            font, pen, etc.) can be done by regenerating the make.label                                                             __________
            command and overwriting the initial file, or by editing the
            text definition file, and using the redo.label command.                                                __________         
            
                 (edit) example:          vi labels/[filename]                                                     ________ 
                                          vi labels/archsites.l                                             __________________
                 
            EXAMPLE            EXAMPLE
            The file labels/archsites.l will display labels from the                     __________________                             
            archsites file in the -sr font, at each archeological site
            location.  The labels will be plotted with the pen in
            position 1, .2 cm high.  Each label will be left justified
            and begin .2 cm away from the actual site location.

